Seadance is located on the Lost Coast of California in the charming oceanside community of Shelter Cove. This beautiful 3bd/3ba 2800 sf oceanfront vacation rental home offers stunning ocean views from nearly every room to help you unwind from your every day life.  Any time of year the Northern California coast is spectacular and the Seadance offers the space, views and relaxing atmosphere to immerse yourself in the glory of nature. Whether you relax to the soothing ocean sounds and/or engage iThe spaceFrom the moment you open the front door, the breathtaking ocean views will capture your attention and set the mood for a relaxing getaway. Â With ocean views from nearly every room in the house, numerous amenities, lovely landscape and so much more, you will appreciate why the Seadance hosts numerous families who return year after year.

â€‹On the main level, captivating views command your attention from the beautiful living area which has comfortable seating areas, Â two full sleeper sofas, full bath and a beautiful fireplace. Also on the main level is a bedroom with a queen bed. Â The kitchen is well equipped with staples on hand - including a variety of spices.Â 

â€‹Upstairs the oceanfront master bedroom has a beautiful view and opens to the balcony and includes a king bed, full bath and sitting area. The third bedroom is across from the master and offers two twin XL beds. Â The third bathroom is on the second level with a claw foot tub and also includes the full size washer/dryer. Â 

The upstairs entertainment area offers another full sofa bed, TV with Roku, DVD/VHS player, hundreds of movies, books and a pool table to challenge friends and family. Â Additional card and board game entertainment can be found in the downstairs cupboard.

Off the main level is a 1000 sf patio, dining area and fire pit to enjoy watching the waves, looking for whales, searching for sea lions and other ocean loving creatures. Â  Want a higher ocean view, hang out on the upstairs balcony.

There are numerous activities within walking distance of Seadance - restaurants, gift and art galleries, deli, nature and fitness trails, tide pools, lighthouse, harbor beach, golf, blow hole and so much more.

The spaceCove Cabin RetreatPeaceful, serene, and secluded, this cabin is the greatest getaway in northern California for outdoor enthusiasts. Private, quiet, and at the end of the road, enjoy the greenery and pure adventure of the forest as you camp with your family and friends. Explore the natural trail right out the back door and experience first-hand the nature and beauty that California has to offer. On your trek, enjoy gorgeous views of the Pacific Ocean and have your breath taken away by the scenery. Enjoy listening to the sounds of the creek, whale watching at the beach, and all other waterfront activities you can think of.

Inside you'll find the all-wooden interior with comfortable furniture to rest your head on after the day's activities. The kitchenette is quaint and perfect for preparing  anything from on-the-go snacks to at-home meals. Your kids, friends, or family will love the fun loft accessible by ladder. There's WiFi in case you need to bring your work with you to your getaway in the woods, a washer/dryer on the back porch, and a tiled shower and tub to wash off the campfire at the end of the day.  This is the ultimate getaway to find peace as you're able to hear the birds, creek, and the ocean.

more description: Nestled among tall majestic trees  sits this tri-level home in beautiful Shelter Cove ready for Guests to enjoy! This home boasts a unique design including a spiral staircase leading to each of the 3 floors, with gorgeous ocean views, and an easy 9 minute walk to Black Sands Beach. Come and experience "Whale Cove Retreat", a 3 bed, 2.5 bath  vacation haven at The Lost Coast you won't forget!The space"Whale Cove Retreat" welcomes you as you step into this beautiful 3 story home!        On the First floor,  you will find the Family room/ game room adorned with nautical themed decor. Pull up the 2 video game chairs and challenge your guests to video games with the SEGA Genesis game console.   And if you need more challenge, step outside to the attached garage where you will find the miniature ping pong table.  On this floor you will find a queen leather sleeper sofa, along with the "kids room" with a twin over full size bunk bed, and a full bathroom with tub shower.          Venture up to the Second floor and be met with spectacular ocean views ! This floor boasts a comfortable living room space, a half bath, and a fully stocked kitchen and dining that will fit your entire group.  Wake up in the  morning with a nice hot cup of coffee and enjoy nature views in the balcony.  In the afternoon, take the family outside onto the deck and BBQ a delicious meal on the easy to use propane grill while being surrounded by  sweeping views of the Pacific Ocean!  Gather together and you may catch glimpses of whale pods!  After a full meal, maybe take an afternoon nap in the  cozy patio lounger and let the sounds of the crashing waves lull you to sleep. In the evening, come inside and snuggle with a book next to the gas fireplace on those chilly nights. Or go outside, turn off all the lights and gaze up at the sky to witness the galaxy of twinkling stars.        Proceed up to the Third floor of the home where you will find the master bedroom with the cozy queen-size bed. The large window allows you to wake up and take in the gorgeous views of the Ocean! There is also an additional small private den/bedroom off to the side which houses a twin size bed in the shape of a boat . This will be a huge hit for the kids or the kid at heart! (Note you will have to walk through the master bedroom to get to this den/bedroom.)   This home is situated in a PERFECT location for exploring Shelter Cove, all within walking distance, or quick car ride. From the house, you can grab a few beach chairs and take an easy (downhill) 9 minute walk to Black Sands Beach. Or if preferred, drive or take a 20 minute leisurely stroll into town where you can get your caffeine buzz at The Fish Tank Expresso Gallery, tidepooling at Mal coombs Park,  meander to the many nature trails, or watch golfers hit a hole-in-one at the beautiful ocean front Shelter Cove Golf course.  The options are endless!    The whole house, with all the amenities, are for your use and enjoyment. This home comes with a  unique spiral staircase accessing each of the 3 floors.  Please note we do not offer baby gates so please plan accordingly if you have toddlers/ children. In the garage, we also offer a bin of outdoor toys including corntoss/bean bag toss game, spike ball, and other sports balls to play on the large park like front yard.  Beach chairs provided. There are a variety of family board games located in the living room and game room. We have left 2 sets of golf clubs for Guests to enjoy if they wish to play at Shelter Cove Golf course; an adult set and a junior set. Great for a Parent/ Child golf outing!  . Washer/ dryer in garage. Outdoor shower to rinse off by side of house. Strong WiFi in the house.  COVID 19 Cleaning practices: We are committed to AIRBNBs five-step enhanced cleaning process that goes beyond basic cleaning to sanitize the entire home.

more description:
The spaceLost Coast HideawayIdeal for that next vacation to the heart of California's Lost Coast, this two-story getaway is a terrific option for those looking to hit the beaches or hike the trails! It is spacious, isolated, nestled in tall trees, and provides a serene escape from the modern world. Inside, discover a well-equipped kitchen, a dining table with plenty of seating for mealtimes or game nights, and two comfortably-furnished living areas. Outside, dine al fresco in the gazebo or check out the view from the upper balcony. You can often see deer, foxes, eagles, and a variety of other birds just looking out of the window. In the garage game room, you'll find a Ping-Pong table for when you're craving a little friendly competition.

Shelter Cove offers breathtaking natural beauty that only the most undeveloped parts of the California coastline can provide. It is a perfect place for those looking to walk the rugged shorelines, enjoy peaceful beaches like the Black Sands Beach, explore the rich tide pools next to the lighthouse, hike the Kings Rangeâ€™s steep mountain trails, or simply relax in nature. For food, we recommend the delicious, locally caught fish at Mi Mochima or the Deliâ€™s unforgettable fish and chips. Gyppo Ale Mill also offers locally brewed beer and a good variety of seasonal entrees. You may also get live Dungeness crabs and fish from local fishermen.

THINGS TO KNOW
Cell service and WiFi can be spotty due to the remote location.
Double sofa bed included.
Guests can enjoy the use of an electric fireplace in the upstairs living room, a Celestron telescope, two yoga mats, two bear cans, camping chairs, left-handed golf clubs, and fishing gear.
Two tri-fold six-inch twin floor mattresses are available for guest use.
TV streaming services require guest accounts to access.
4x4 vehicles are recommended.2 dog(s)  are welcome in this home. No other animals are allowed without specific Vacasa approval.Parking notes: There is free parking for 3 vehicles. Space in the driveway, small parking space parallel to the road, and a spare lot next to the house. The garage is not available for parking.  Damage waiver: The total cost of your reservation for this Property includes a damage waiver fee which covers you for up to $3,000 of accidental damage to the Property or its contents (such as furniture, fixtures, and appliances) as long as you report the incident to the host prior to checking out. More information can be found from the "Additional rules" on the checkout page.County permit number:EXEMPTCounty tax number:13557

more description: Situated on 40 acres hillside, our solar-powered off-grid cabin presents gorgeous views of King Range. Quite, private, and relaxing getaway will be memorable with birds, crickets, and frogs all around making themselves heard.The spaceThe Cabin is secluded on almost 40 acres in the coastal mountains on a beautiful hillside hidden behind old Oaks, with a middle-of-nowhere, up above the clouds appeal. It is around 7 miles out of Garberville, the last 1 Â½ miles is on a private well-maintained dirt road. All wheel drive or SUV is recommended. Built in 70s and recently remodeled, the house offers a contemporary open-floor design, high ceilings and skylights for plenty of natural light. Downstairs includes a kitchen, dining area, living room, and two large decks. Upstairs there is two open rooms, one bedroom, and a loft each with queen beds.  The full kitchen includes granite counters, new cabinets and modern appliances: range, oven, full refrigerator/freezer. China set for eight, glassware, cups, silverware, pots, pans and utensils are available. There's plenty of counter prep space. The living room has amazing views, a wood stove fireplace, and an alcove. This open space is ideal for working, entertaining and relaxation.The bedroom presents a luxurious queen bed with very comfortable, high quality, medium-firm mattress. There's a dresser and a night stand. The second bedroom/loft has a queen bed with a medium/plush firmness mattress. Also, there is a dresser and a closet with plenty of shelving. The third spare twin bed is downstairs tucked in semi-private area. All beds have soft and luxurious fitted 300-thread count Brooklinen's Egyptian cotton sheets.The bathroom has old woods charm, custom made windows, the shower is in a claw foot tub fitted with a handheld shower head and requires some agility to get in and out. It is simple, with wood floors. Our water comes from a gravity fed spring and can have some natural sediments after the rain. For your convenience, there is a laundry room, and plenty off-street parking on our driveway.The cabin has a cat door!!!

name: Home in Whitethorn
unit rental details: Entire home hosted byÂ Katie12 guests Â·  Â· 4 bedrooms Â·  Â· 11 beds Â·  Â· 3 baths
number of guests: 12 guests Â· **__** Â· 4 bedrooms Â· **__** Â· 11 beds Â· **__** Â· 3 baths**__**Joined in June 2019**__**PrivacyÂ·**__**Â·TermsÂ·**__**Â·Sitemap**__**PrivacyÂ·**__**Â·TermsÂ·**__**Â·Sitemap**__**PrivacyÂ·**__**Â·TermsÂ·**__**Â·Sitemap
more description: Blacksands at Shelter Cove is an amazing retreat for your next family trip!  The house is located 1/2 mile from the famous Black Sands Beach on the lost coast. * Gourmet Kitchen* Great Room with 20-foot ceilings* Movie Theatre/ game room- 3D/ HD 130 inch screen, immersive surround sound, also a 65 inch TV + ping pong + darts.* Stamped Concrete floors with the radiant floor heating *4  Bedrooms- 11 beds* Hottub* Great fenced back yard- turf, covered patio.* 7 TVs! * WiFi * Spa-like bathThe spaceBlackSands at Shelter Cove is located 1/2 mile from the famous Black Sands beach on the Lost Coast. This is a great house for multiple families to enjoy their time in Shelter Cove. The house is a pet-friendly house with a unique backyard for them to run around. Here are the top 10 reasons families will LOVE BlackSands1. You will love to explore the four levels of the house. There is plenty of space to spread out, and the great room is perfect for gathering. The island can seat seven people + 5 dining table + 8 person table. The Great Room has power reclining couches seating 6. The layout of the house is perfect for multiple families. 2. You will  LOVE the seven-person hot tub enjoying the peaceful views of the woods.3. You will  LOVE the bunk room. Whether playing games, watching a movie, or drawing on the chalkboard. It's great to take all the kids and put them in one room. 4. You will love the Movie theatre /game room. Why?? 65-inch tv, 130-inch 3D movie screen for movie night, dartboard, ping pong, movies, games, and the chalkboard. This room has an Immersive surround sound for music and movies 5. You will love hiking to Black Sand beach 6. Your kids will love to play in the back yard. The artificial turf looks like grass but not. It is soft and clean, so your kiddos don't get all dirty.7. You will love the art room to paint and draw or create an abalone/ shell wall art. 8.  You will enjoy going to the tide pools and beaches. Collecting abalone shells, which you can see displayed all over the house, is a favorite activity for our children. You can make all sorts of craft projects with the shells. 9. You will love watching movies in the great room with an extensive 75â€ TV and impressive seven-speaker in-wall surround sound system. 10. You will enjoy hiking the Lost Coast trail from Black Sands beach or walking through the redwood forest.More info about the house:The house faces the south, so it gets direct sunlight for most of the day.  The house is newly constructed and finished in Jan of 2020.  The architectural style is unique, in that it is built almost entirely of concrete with 12-inch walls and stamped concrete radiant heated floors. The house has four levels and 3350ft2. We are about 300 feet above sea level, and 1/2 mile from the water, which is just far enough from the water to have a safe place for kids to play and you get better weather (more sun, less wind, and fog), but you can still hear the sounds of the waves below. You are surrounded by a beautiful view of fir trees and lush green vegetation from the wetland that extends in the back of the property.  As you pull up to the house, you will see the entrance and a patio to the right. Some stairs take you to the main level and front door. You can also enter the house on the 4th level, which is a Movie theatre/game room. Here is a favorite spot to hang out and enjoy a game of ping pong or throw darts. Also, a floor to ceiling chalkboard is super fun for the kids. The movie theatre screen is 130 inches 3D /HD, and you have fantastic immersive surround sound. We have an assortment of 3D and regular blue rays movies. The system is also connected to DirectTV. There is a second 65 inch TV so that you can watch two games at the same time!You can bring your gaming system and easily connect to either TV with extra HDMI cables.This room can also serve as a 5th bedroom and has a queen futon, and we have two queen air mattresses. This room can sleep 4-6. If used as a bedroom, you can use the front door at the primary level to enter the house. Letâ€™s continue the tour-You enter the central part of the house and descend several stairs to the 3rd level. The house has an open concept, so you are looking down into the great room and see the five massive windows that provide views of the forest and wetland. Overlooking the great room is the desk that is custom made from a slab of Walnut. You will have access to the 27inch mac for any work that you need to do during your stay. You will see many accents, railings, and shelves that are custom made from local hardwoods.  Also, you will see the 25-foot walls in the great room, clad with shiplap. The room has an open, light, and grand feel to it. Going past the desk leads you into the Master Bedroom. Here there are windows with shutters that open to the great room below. Also, a balcony off the master bedroom overlooks the backyard 20 feet below. You can listen to the waves from Black Sands Beach and watch the stars that are fantastically bright on the Lost Coast. The room has a king-size bed and a couch that opens into a queen bed. There is a 55 inch TV, and the room sleeps 4 comfortably. The bathroom ensuite in the master is very lovely with a soaker tub, his and her sinks and a large walk-in shower with a multi soaker shower.The stairs lead down to the main level of the house (level 2). Here you will see the Great Room that features power reclining couches and a 75 inch 4k TV with seven-speaker surround sound. We love to watch movies or listen to music. The sound system is connected to Alexa for voice commands, "Hey Alexa Play Johny Cash." The Kitchen extends the great room and has a massive island that is a favorite spot to watch the chefs cook the fresh catch of the day. The kitchen has all the amenities to cook a great meal. Also the great room as 2 kitchen tables, seating 7-8 at the main and six at the smaller. The total sitting spots, including the coach and island, is over 20. The dining area has a slider that leads to a covered balcony where you will find the BBQ and views of the forest. A spiral staircase just off the side patio will lead you to the back yard and 1st level. Back through the great room leads you past the front door and entryway to the guest room and second bathroom. The bathroom is clad with shiplap and has a bathtub and shower. The guest room has a queen bed with a view of the forest. There is a 55 inch TV. The room has a reading nook that can also serve as a twin bed and can sleep 3. Just to the right of the guest rooms is the linen closet, and adjacent to this is a walk-in pantry. We have a refrigerator here, where we keep our food. The  Kitchen has a pantry and pantry that will be empty for guests. From the main level, you go down to the first floor. There is a small art room where you can get your creative juices flowing. You can paint rocks, a picture, or make a shell board. Right next to the art room is the bunk room. A large barn door separates this bedroom and is an excellent spot for the kids or a family. The room has 2 bunk beds (full on the bottom and twin of the top). There is an entertainment system to watch TV or play movies on a  55 inch TV. The room has a super comfy carpet and a chalkboard on the wall. The sliding door leads you to the backyard witch we will go over in a few. This room sleeps 6.The room next to the bunk room is the 4th bedroom and has a queen bed and another reading nook that can serve as a twin bed. This room also has a 55-inch tv. The sliding door provides excellent views of the backyard and forest. The bathroom on the first level has a shower with multi-panel massage jets. The room adjacent to this is the boiler room. Here is the system that heats the house. The heating system wouldn't usually be something to mention in a rental, but this system is pretty cool. There is over a mile of pex tubing that runs under the stamped concrete floors. There are four zones in the house, each controlled with a Nest thermostat. The feeling of warm floors under your feet is lovely after coming back from a day at the beach. You can control the temperature of the house from the nest app or Alexa. We can remotely turn on the heat to your desired temperature before your arrival. The backyard has a covered stamped concrete patio with a hot tub to relax after a day at the tide pools. Also, a 600 FT2 turf lawn is a great place to enjoy a game of corn hole and is perfect for kids to play around on, without getting dirty. You donâ€™t have the worries of being too close to the water if you have little kids. The grass is enclosed by a fence and is about 4 feet above the wetland. Here are some top things to do in Shelter Cove1. Visit the redwoods. If you are driving from the Bay Area, you can make a stop in Leggett, which has the drive-through tree. Just past Garberville is the Avenue of the Giants. There is also a small grove just past Redway on the way to Shelter Cove. This would be the closest grove to the house, which is about 20 miles; 35-40 min.2. Black Sand Beach- a great place to walk and watch the sunset. Not a swimming beach.3. Shelter Cove Beach- you can drive on this beach at low tide. A recommendation is to check the tides each day and plan accordingly. There are two low tides each day, with one being smaller than the other. We time our beach arrival or tide pools for low tide. This is an excellent beach for swimming, paddleboard, and kayaking. 4. Malcolm Park- this is is the area with the Lighthouse. We like to picnic here, and there is a huge picnic table that can seat 12 people. Take the stairs down to a small beach and tide pools, but check the tides so that you can time your arrival, and you are fortunate is you go on a negative tide. The tide pools extend from Molcoms and north for about 1/2 mile to Abalone point. The tide pools have amazing creatures and seals are all over the place. You can find some tremendous Abalone shells (donâ€™t take live ones); also, you can pull mussels off the rocks and boil with white wine and butter.5. Golf- there is a nine-hole golf course around the runway. There are a couple of sets of old golf clubs that you can use. They are under the stairs. 6. Biking- Paradise Park is Mountain bike park that is about 5 miles up Shelter Cove road. This has single track trails and a bike park with obstacles. You can also ride bikes on the street in front of the house. 7. ATV- people like riding motorcycles and ATVs throughout the town and on the beach. You will see this more on holiday weekends and not so much during a typical week.  If youâ€™ve got one, bring it, and you will enjoy it. 8. Fishing- Shelter cove is a well-known fishing spot. There is room to park a boat in front of the house. You can also charter a fishing boat from a couple of local operators. We have a fishing pole you can use with the kayak. 9. Whale Watching- Whale watching in Shelter Cove peaks in April and May during the grey whaleâ€™s migration down the Pacific Coast to warmer waters. You can charter a boat or watch the spouts from any number of picnic spots along the cove.10. Watch the planes land- Shelter Cove has a small runway.  There is no tower, and itâ€™s not monitored. Private pilots will fly to Shelter Cove, which must be awesome. 11. Gyppos- this is our local brewery and restaurant. It overlooks the runway and golf course. They have an outside gas fire pit that is a favorite spot for a cold beer. They have live music and a helpful website that feature the activities for the week. They have corn hole and other games, and the kids can play on the grass around the golf course. 12. Fish Bowl- This is the local coffee shop, and a must-see on your trip. Itâ€™s located at the Inn of the Lost Coast. Great coffee and I love the salmon bagel with the works. The owners are super friendly and will give you tips or can connect you with charters or anything else. Autumn knows everyone and knows everything about the cove.13.Delgato Pizza- this is also located at the hotel. You can order a take out pizza from here, or they have a couple of tables outside. They also have baked goods. 14. Skyâ€™s- this is the newest restaurant in the cove. Great tai food and incredible views. This is also a BYOB establishment so that you can save some $$ on your alcohol bill.15. Mi Mochimo- this is a cool Venezuela restaurant that is across from the Hotel. Great deck and unique dishes.

more description: Ready for an adventure, escape it all with a vacation to southern Humboldt! Sweet recently built, two bedroom and one bathroom craftsman home with hardwood floors. Located in the eclectic town of Garberville, in a quiet neighborhood.  The house is perfect location, five minute walk to restaurants, shops, bar, natural food store and more!  One hour drive to Shelter Cove on the Lost Coast or one hour to Ferndale and Arcata. Come to explore the Redwoods and experience the culture of Humboldt!The spaceThe house is newly built and features hardwood floors and open kitchen living room area with an island and cafe table to dine at.  There is a coffee maker, (I provide raw sugar and filters) and a coffee grinder for all my whole bean guests;)The house has air conditioning and heat. The living area has a TV with ROKU to watch all your favorite streaming platforms also a DVD player. The first larger bedroom has a king sized bed and small patio through slider doors.  The second bedroom has a queen bed.  Both rooms use only cotton sheets and cotton duvet covers.  Small closets in each room have extra towels, washcloths, blankets and iron.  No need to strip beds or take out trash, we have great help that does everything to clean up after your stay! There is a washer and dryer in the garage for your use as well.  Landscaped small front yard with porch and fully fenced yard with a front gate that can be closed for extra privacy. The driveway holds two vehicles(back out slowly in to the street).

more description: Sea View at Shelter Cove was freshly remodeled in 2018 & decorated with all new furnishings & accessories. The tropical & beach inspired dÃ©cor compliments the gorgeous ocean view & spacious decks offer sunset views. Find your perfect Lost Coast vacation home here in this beautiful location on a quiet street, with enchanting ocean views.The ocean, golf course, landing strip, nature trails, fishing, surfing, restaurants, & more are within a short walk.The spaceSea View at Shelter Cove was freshly remodeled in 2018. The home features brand new flooring, fresh paint, new vanities, toilets, light fixtures, and all new furnishings and accessories. The tropical and beach inspired dÃ©cor compliments the gorgeous ocean view the home offers. This single level home includes a spacious living room with sectional sofa, cozy chairs, a gas fireplace, and an ocean view; a master bedroom with queen size bed and attached full bathroom; the "Sandcastle" room which features a bunk bed set with a full size bed on the bottom and twin on the top; the den which has a  fold down futon sofa bed, houses the TV and DVD player, and is stocked with DVDs, books, tons of puzzles, and games; a full guest bathroom with tub and shower; full kitchen with dishes, glasses, flat wear, and pots and pans; a dining room with seating for six, a mud room, and a game room in the garage featuring ping pong and darts. Outdoor living is encouraged with an ample sized back and front decks for sunset views. The ocean, golf course, conveniences, nature trails, and more are within walking distance of this property. Visitors enjoy the local surf spots, black sands beach, fishing, hiking, golfing, and simply relaxing in Shelter Cove. Enjoy activities or simply the peaceful and quiet community that is Shelter Cove. A nearby landing strip accommodates small planes.Notes: WIFI is very limited. Appropriate for checking email and basic browsing. We recommend turning the WIFI calling feature on your cellphone to improve cell reception. Though we can sleep 7 please check that the beds we are providing will be suitable for your needs. For example the bunks are a twin and a full which may be comfortable for 3 children to share but not three adults. The bed in the den is a convertible sofa bed. Please see pictures to ensure these accommodations meet your needs.

more description:
The spaceHappy Hill RetreatFind solitude and adventure in California's Lost Coast at this beautiful, two-bedroom retreat. Boasting whitewater ocean views and accommodations to sleep four adults comfortably, plus two child-friendly options, this home is the perfect option for a family getaway. Enjoy a private setting with walkable access to to the beach. Lounge in the hammock on the expansive deck or fire up the private gas grill for a barbecue with an unforgettable view. The full-size kitchen comes well-equipped to handle family meals, with stainless steel appliances and utensils. The garage has been converted into a gym/fitness room, including a sauna for ultimate relaxation and luxury after a day exploring the area. Cap off the evening cozied up by the living room fireplace to stream your favorite movies and shows on the flatscreen smart TV.

Great food, drinks, and attractions abound within easy reach of the home. Local standouts include Gyppos Brew House, Mi Mochima, Delgada Pizza, and the Fish Tank. Black Sands Beach and the Lost Coast trail offer world-class hiking and mountain biking. Stop by Briceland Winery for a glass of local wine before heading back home.

more description: Kick back and relax in our cozy home on the Lost Coast. It features a fun outdoor space with grill station, fire pit, hammock, and table tennis. It's a short walk to the Mattole River where you can take a dip in the clear water, bask in the sun, take a spin on the paddle board, or cast a fly.  The home is centrally located with easy access to the town of Petrolia, the Lost Coast Trail, King Range National Conservation Area, and Humboldt Redwoods State Park.The spaceOur space is small, clean, and cozy and lots of fun. It is set up for those that love to cook, inside and out. The backyard is where we spend most of our time. Play a board game on the deck or some lawn games under the big Mattole sky, stargaze on the hammock at night while roasting some marshmallows on the fire, or play a late night game of table tennis with some mellow beats. We provide beach chairs, beach towels, a paddle board, and a beach cart for hanging down at the river. There are also a couple of bikes for cruising the neighborhood. We have so many great memories raising our two sons on the Mattole and hope you can continue to create more!

more description: Welcome to the Redwood Forest! Where they say location is everything! You are going to love being within walking distance to great restaurants, bars, groceries, convenience stores, post office, hardware stores, gas stations, river trails, and park. You will be in the heart of the Redwood forest close to the entrance of Avenue of Giants, Humboldt Redwoods state park, Shelter Cove. Come and discover nearby sightseeing, wander the scenic north coast, or explore the redwoods just outside your room.The spaceThis is a newly remodeled Inn close to great sights. more description: Our small family farm invites you to camp in luxury under a canopy of redwoods. Located just 10 mins outside of Garberville in a redwood valley, we offer two glamping sites that have everything you need to enjoy nature in style. One of the sites is called The Orchard. You can drive your car right up to it. The other requires climbing stairs to the top of a hill. We call that one The Knoll. This page describes The Orchard site. See my other listings to view more info on The Knoll.The spaceThe Orchard Site features a carpeted 16 foot round tent with a queen size bed with all linens, pillows blankets, as well as a couch, coffee table, drawers for clothing, and solar powered lights both inside and outside. It has a small outdoor kitchenette with a 2-burner stove, pots, pans, coffee, tea, and a 5-gallon water jug. Enjoy your meals on a large outdoor table nestled under a shade awning. Plates, glasses and cutlery are provided. There is a cooler, a compost bin for your food scraps, porto-potty service and a hand washing station. more description: Welcome to the Benbow Historic Inn, a premiere North Coast Hotel, Golf Course and KOA RV resort located near Garberville â€“ a small town in the heart of California Redwood Country near the Avenue of the Giants. Nestled on the banks of the Eel River in Humboldt County, California. Our resort offers something for everyone seeking a California Redwoods vacation.Enjoy a delicious meal in our fabulous dining room or outdoor dining under the canopy of the redwoods.The spaceAbout This RoomView of back terrace, stone bridge, tree tops. Gas fireplace, desk with outlet and vaulted ceilings.The room includes a king size bed, luxuriously large bathroom with a soaking tub.  A variety of artisan bath bombs, bubble bath, and soaps are available at the gift shop to complete a relaxing night away from home.About Jessie BenbowJessie was the third Benbow child. She was dark and dramatic and left home as soon as she could, living with her musical cousins in Petrolia and performing for guests at the Petrolia hotel. When the family decided to buy the ranch, Jessie and her husband Harold pitched in with all the dirty work, driving tractors, burning bushes, digging trenches. She assisted in the kitchen, at the Front Desk, cleaned rooms, washed laundry, and worked with the seamstresses. She loved the color lavender which will be evident in her room.
